  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `v1.10.6`\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nIt is mentioned in the [RPC spec](https://playground.open-rpc.org/?uiSchema%5BappBar%5D%5Bui:splitView%5D=false&schemaUrl=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ethereum/eth1.0-specs/master/json-rpc/spec.json&uiSchema%5BappBar%5D%5Bui:input%5D=false) that for `eth_feeHistory` block tags (e.g. `earliest`, `latest`, `pending`) are supported\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nAn error is returned when attempting to use any block tag:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n  \"id\": 0,\r\n  \"error\": {\r\n    \"code\": -32602,\r\n    \"message\": \"invalid argument 0: json: cannot unmarshal string into Go value of type int\"\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd the [method implementation](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/internal/ethapi/api.go#L90) seems to be expecting an `int`\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\"method\": \"eth_feeHistory\",\"params\": [\"0x4\",\"latest\",[]],\"id\": 0}'\r\n```",
